cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on grammatical relationships. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses different learning techniques and the effectiveness of different measures, which suggests that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of memory-based learning, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
